{
  "texts": [
    "Comparatively, GPT-4 may exhibit higher accuracy in the task of drug target prediction compared to GPT -3.5.",
    "For example, naltrexone, a medication used to manage alcohol or opioid dependence, blocks the effects of opioids in the brain to reduce cravings.",
    "It acts as an antagonist for OPRK1 (opioid receptor kappa 1) and as an agonist for OPRM1 (opioid receptor mu 1) and SIGMAR1 (sigma non-opioid intracellular receptor 1).",
    "GPT-3.5 only recorded the OPRM1 target, disregarding the other protein targets.",
    "In contrast, GPT-4 recorded the OPRM1 target correctly identified the primary target, OPRK1 (Fig. 4).Another phenomenon observed in the target prediction task is 'illusory knowledge construction' and 'knowledge hallucination.'"
  ]
}